---

## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Here we have to do 4 types of traversal to get the spiral matrix.
    1. First row from left to right.
    2. Last column from top to down.
    3. Last row from right to left.
    4. First column from down to top.
- We will take 4 pointers: ***top, down, left, right*** & 1 counter ***count*** to select the traversal type.
    - If ***count=0,*** we will traverse a row from left to right & increase count value.
    - If ***count=1,*** we will traverse a column from top to down & increase count value.
    - If ***count=2,*** we will traverse a row from right to left & increase count value.
    - If ***count=3,*** we will traverse a column from down to top & will make ***count=0*** to repeat the traversal again.
- We’ll repeat the process until ***top<=down && left<=right.***
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> spiralOrder(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        vector<int> ans;
        int n= matrix[0].size(), m= matrix.size();

        int top=0,down=m-1,left=0,right=n-1, count=0;

        while(top<=down && left<=right){
            if(count==0){
                for(int i=left; i<=right; i++)
                    ans.push_back(matrix[top][i]);
                top++; count++;
            }
            else if(count==1){
                for(int i=top; i<=down; i++)
                    ans.push_back(matrix[i][right]);
                right--; count++;
            }
            else if(count==2){
                for(int i=right; i>=left; i--)
                    ans.push_back(matrix[down][i]);
                down--; count++;
            }
            else if(count==3){
                for(int i=down; i>=top; i--)
                    ans.push_back(matrix[i][left]);
                left++; count=0;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

