# Approach
Initialize variables:

n is the number of rows in the matrix.
m is the number of columns in the matrix.
startrow, startcol, endrow, and endcol are pointers to represent the boundaries of the current spiral.
total is the total number of elements in the matrix (n * m).
count is used to keep track of the number of elements added to the result vector ans.
Use a while loop that runs as long as count is less than total, indicating that not all elements have been traversed yet.

Traverse the matrix in four steps:
a. Starting row: Traverse from left to right in the current startrow from startcol to endcol.
b. Ending column: Traverse from top to bottom in the current endcol from startrow to endrow.
c. Ending row: Traverse from right to left in the current endrow from endcol to startcol.
d. Starting column: Traverse from bottom to top in the current startcol from endrow to startrow.

After each step, update the corresponding boundary (startrow, startcol, endrow, endcol) to move towards the center of the matrix. Also, increment the count by the number of elements traversed in that step.

Repeat the above steps until all elements are traversed (count == total).

Return the ans vector containing the spiral order traversal of the matrix.

Note: The code assumes that the input matrix is non-empty and a valid 2D matrix (i.e., all rows have the same number of elements). If the input matrix is empty or has different-sized rows, the code might encounter undefined behavior.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:0(n*m)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:0(n*m)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> spiralOrder(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
         vector<int>ans;
        int m = matrix[0].size();
        int startrow=0;
        int startcol=0;
        int endrow=n-1;
        int endcol=m-1;
        int total=n*m;
        int count =0;
        while(count<total)
        {
            // starting row 
            for(int i = startcol; count<total && i<=endcol;i++)
            {
                ans.push_back(matrix[startrow][i]);
                count++;
            }
            startrow++;
            // ending col
            for(int i = startrow; count<total && i<=endrow;i++)
            {
                ans.push_back(matrix[i][endcol]);
                count++;
            }
            endcol--;
            // ending row
            for(int i = endcol; count<total && i>=startcol;i--)
            {
                ans.push_back(matrix[endrow][i]);
                count++;
            }
            endrow--;
            // starting col
            for(int i = endrow; count<total && i>=startrow;i--)
            {
                ans.push_back(matrix[i][startcol]);
                count++;
            }
            startcol++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

