# Intuition & Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Initialize four variables: l, r, t, b, representing the start and end indices of the rows and columns of the submatrix we are currently traversing.
2. Traverse the top row from left to right, incrementing the column index  at each step. When the traversal reaches the last column, update the t variable to move down to the next row.
3. Traverse the right column from top to bottom, decrementing the row index at each step. When the traversal reaches the last row, update the r variable to move to the next column.
4. Traverse the bottom row from right to left, decrementing the column index at each step. When the traversal reaches the first column, update the b variable to move up to the next row.
5. Traverse the left column from bottom to top, incrementing the row index at each step. When the traversal reaches the first row, update the l variable to move to the next column.

Repeat steps 2-5 until all elements have been traversed.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N*M)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> spiralOrder(int[][] arr) {
        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        int b = arr.length, r = arr[0].length;
        int t = 0, l = 0, size = b*r;
        while(t<=b && l<=r){
            for (int i = l; i < r; i++) {
                res.add(arr[t][i]);
            }
            t++;
            for (int i = t; i < b; i++) {
                res.add(arr[i][r-1]);
            }
            r--;
            if(res.size()>=size){
                break;
            }
            for (int i = r-1; i >= l; i--) {
                res.add(arr[b-1][i]);
            }
            b--;
            if(res.size()>=size)
                break;
            for (int i = b-1; i >= t; i--) {
                res.add(arr[i][l]);
            }
            l++;
            if(res.size()>=size)
                break;

        }
        return res;

    }
}

```

