* The idea is to maintain **4 boolean variables right, down, left, up** which will tell us in which direction to move. 
* There are **4 integer variables rowStart, rowEnd, colStart, colEnd** to specify constrains for moving in single direction. After moving in any direction update these variables to move in another direction.
* The **index** variable will be incremented at each time so that **r*c** matrix cells will be stored in linear array
* Adjust the constrains based upon direction of traversing n these values can be used in **while condition**
	* After traversing in horitanzal direction from left to right **rowStart** will increment by one
	* After  traversing in horitanzal direction from right to left **rowEnd** will decrement by one
	* After traversing in vertical direction from top to bottom **colEnd** will decrement by one
	* After traversing in vertical direction from bottom to top **colStart** will increment by one
