solutions.content:
**Approach 1st**

**Idea**
Assume the array is circular and find an index having element smaller then the previous ones! else return the arr[0] as it might be that all elements are same!!

**Time Complexity**
O(n)

````
class Solution {
    public int findMin(int[] arr) {

        int i,n=arr.length;
        for(i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(i==n-1)
            {
                if(arr[i]>arr[0])
                    return arr[0];
            }
            else
            {
                if(arr[i]>arr[i+1])
                    return arr[i+1];
            }
        }
        return arr[0];
    }
}
````

**Approach 2nd**

**Idea**
Using Binary Search

**Starting** ->
**If arr[i]<arr[j]** is true that mean array is not rotated even once!!!

**During Binary Search Algorithm**->
**if arr[mid]> arr[j] then i=mid+1** is true that mean min element is at right side of the array and why i=mid+1 because arr[mid] can not be the answer that why we increase it by one!!

**else if(arr[mid]<arr[j]) then j=mid** is true that mean min element is at left side of the array and why j=mid beacuse arr[mid] can be the answer as it smaller then arr[j]!!!

**else i.e arr[mid]==arr[j] then j--** means that min element is at left side only as this condition if(arr[mid>arr[j]]) was failed so that why we reduce left index by one!!!

**Why we are returning arr[j]?** 

Because at j will contain index of smallest element -> **How?**
See carefully we are storing j=mid when arr[mid]<arr[j] and this mid will always have element smaller then jth index so j=mid!!!
And in case of i we storing i=mid+1 when arr[mid]>arr[j] and this mid will never have the smallest element and if mid+1 contains the smallest elements then in next iterate it will manage by second condition i.e if(arr[i]<arr[j]) then j=mid!!!

**Time Complexity**
O(n) In considering all elements are same 

````
class Solution {
    public int findMin(int[] arr) {

        int i=0,j=arr.length-1;
        if(arr[i]<arr[j])
            return arr[i];
        while(i<j)
        {
            int mid=i+(j-i)/2;
            if(arr[mid]>arr[j])
                i=mid+1;
            else  if(arr[mid]<arr[j])
                j=mid;
            else 
                j--;
        }
        return arr[j];
    }
}
````
