# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We can approach the solution by using Two Pointers.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
First we take `min` as `Integer.MAX_VALUE` then we traverse the array `nums` using two pointers `low` and `high` which we set as `0` and `nums.length - 1`.

when `low <= high` , we check if the value of low is less than the value of min then we update min as `nums[low]`.
same with the value of high is less than the value of the min then wee update the min as `nums[high]`.

then we **increase** the low pointer and **decrease** the high pointer.

at the end of the array we will be having the `min` value.

