# Intuition
 ## Plz upvote if you find this useful
# > This problem is similar to find minimum in rotated and sorted array(153).
the only difference is that in this problem duplicate element can come.
As array is sorted so we can think something like binary search.

# Approach````
code
````
Take strating index s=0,ending index=size of array -1.

Every time we'll be checking if the nums[mid]>nums[e], then we can say that our minimum element will be in left part i.e s=mid+1.

Else we'll check if num[mid]<nums[e] then we can find minimum element in right part. But here we are initialising e=mid because there might be case in which our nums[mid]=minimum element.

 If we do e=mid-1,we'll end up searching in the wrong part.
But wait nums may contain duplictes so if nums[mid]==nums[e] then we simply decrease e i.e e-- to tackle duplicates.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
log n

- Space complexity:
o(1) constant space

# Code

class Solution {
public:
    int findMin(vector<int>& nums) {
        int s=0,e=nums.size()-1,mid=(s+e)/2;
        while(s<e){
            if(nums[mid]>nums[e]) //min ele in left part
                s=mid+1;
            else if(nums[mid]<nums[e]) //min element in right part
                e=mid;
            else // to remove duplicates  elemnt
            e--;
            mid=(s+e)/2; //updting **Bold**mid
        }
        return nums[s];
    }
};
```

