// this is nlogn lis variant
we need to sort the weights in increasing order but if they are equal then
   heights should be in decreasing order , this is done to ensure that when we
   do lis on the height the lower one do not gets picked up. eg

   [[5,4],[6,5],[6,7],[2,3]]

