solutions.content:
My initial approach was to add another value to each letter, the maximum amount of letters you can wrap in.

Going through them, after having them sorted from the smallest (width-wise and with extra condition for the height), we would then get how each one can fit into the others.

To do so, we declare a single support variable `res`, initialised to `1` (even if no letter fits into any other, you would still have a single letter on his own as a minimum amount to consider valid).

We would then sort `envelopes` and add to each of them `1` (again, the minimum series of envelopes you can wrap in - a single envelope).

Now time to find the matches between fitting envelopes!

We will loop with `i` through all the envelopes but the last one and:
* assign `cix`, `ciy` and `ciq` respectively as the propery of the enveoped pointed by `i`;
* loop with `j` throught all the envelopes from `i + ` to the last one and:
	* assign `cjx`, `cjy` and `cjq` respectively as the propery of the enveoped pointed by `j`;
	* if there is a fit (`cjx > cix && cjy > ciy`), update the maximum size as the max between the current value (`ciq`) and the new one (`ciq + 1`);
	* update `res` as the maximum value between its current one and the new one we just updated.

Once done, we can return `res` :)

The code:

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxEnvelopes(vector<vector<int>>& envelopes) {
        // support variables
        int res = 1;
        // preparing envelopes
        sort(begin(envelopes), end(envelopes));
        for (auto &e: envelopes) e.push_back(1);
        // matching envelopes
        for (int i = 0, lmti = envelopes.size() - 1, cix, ciy, ciq; i < lmti; i++) {
            cix = envelopes[i][0], ciy = envelopes[i][1], ciq = envelopes[i][2];
            for (int j = i + 1, lmtj = lmti + 1, cjx, cjy, cjq; j < lmtj; j++) {
                cjx = envelopes[j][0], cjy = envelopes[j][1], cjq = envelopes[j][2];
                if (cjx > cix && cjy > ciy) envelopes[j][2] = max(cjq, ciq + 1);
                res = max(res, envelopes[j][2]);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

