Came up with this different approach to the problem. I figured we could model these envelopes as a graph where an edge from n1 -> n2 would mean that n1 can envelope n2 [n1.width > n2.width && n1.height > n2.height]. Now that we have the graph, we can find the longest path and the length of that would give us the answer. I cached the longest path from nodes to avoid recurring subproblems, to avoid TLE. 

Runtime : 1131ms. faster than 5% of the submissions
Memory: 111.4mb, less than 7.69% of the submissions

Definitely not the best approach but a possible one. 

