First, we need to sort. Because we would like to get a sequence that the smallest size envelop should be on the left side of the array. Then, it can easier determine whether next envelop could / could not wrap it. The evelopes on its left cannot do that.

For the DP:

the dp[i] means for the envelop `i`, the maximun envelopes it can contain.

`dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1); j : [0, i);`

because for each i, it may has different ways to wrap. But we do not know which way is the best.

```javascript
var maxEnvelopes = function(envelopes) {
    envelopes.sort((a, b) => {
        if (a[0] === b[0]) {
            return a[1] - b[1];
        }
        return a[0] - b[0];
    });
    const dp = new Array(envelopes.length); // dp[i], i 这个位置的信封，能装的最多的信。
    dp.fill(1);
    let max = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < envelopes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (envelopes[i][0] > envelopes[j][0] && envelopes[i][1] > envelopes[j][1]) {
                dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1);
            }
        }
        max = Math.max(max, dp[i]);
    }
    return max;
};
```

