The question at first might sound different to you once you go through it (atleast it sound me difficult at first), but its approach is way simple.
***Intuition:-***
Look at this example,
[[1,2,2,1],[3,1,2],[1,3,2],[2,4],[3,1,2],[1,3,1,1]]

Just focus on the first row, you will found that the 1st brick ends at width 1, 2nd brick ends at width 3, 3rd brich ends at width 5 and last brick ends at width 6. Thus if you start drawing the vertical line from position 1,3,5,6 than you are not crossing any brick in row 1. Now find this thing for every row.

You will get :-
1 3 5 6
3 4 6
1 4 6
2 6
3 4 6
1 4 5 6

Here I have shown the ending width of last brick but it is mentioned that we should not consider this,
***You cannot draw a line just along one of the two vertical edges of the wall, in which case the line will obviously cross no bricks.***

1 3 5
3 4
1 4
2
3 4
1 4 5

We are left with these values, store these value as key and their frequency in a map.

Let n   = wall.size();
Find max frequency in the map let it be maxFreq.
and return n - maxFreq.

The maxFreq element shows the edge of the bricks in different rows that are ending at that location, i.e. if we draw our line at the location corresponding to the keye of maxFreq in map, that maxFreq number of bricks will not be cut.
Thus bricks that will cut are
n - maxFreq

```
class Solution {
public:
    int leastBricks(vector<vector<int>>& wall) {
        int n = wall.size();
        if(n == 0){
            return 0;
        }

        unordered_map<int,int> mp;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int sumBias = 0;
            for(int j=0;j<wall[i].size()-1;j++){
                int currWidth = sumBias + wall[i][j];
                if(mp.find(currWidth) == mp.end()){
                    mp[currWidth] = 1;
                }else{
                    mp[currWidth]++;
                }
                sumBias += wall[i][j];
            }

        }

        unordered_map<int,int>::iterator it;
        int maxFreq = 0;
        int maxCut = 0;

        for(it=mp.begin();it!=mp.end();it++){
            int currCut = it->first;
            int currFreq = it->second;
            if(currFreq > maxFreq){
                maxFreq = currFreq;
                maxCut = currCut;
            }
        }
        return n-maxFreq;
    }
};
```

